description:
The stunning final arc of SCALPED continues here with "Trail's End" part 2. Months have passed on the Rez since the fight between Dash and Shunka, and it seems that peace has finally settled in. But this is life on the Prairie Rose. Peace doesn't last forever...

General note: Diesel appears in flashbacks and as a skeleton.
name: Trail's End, Part Two

description: 'Kittens vs. Robots,' Part 2! It's bad enough that an army of TSA security robots have gone on a rampage in downtown Manhattan. But add the mysterious flying ring disks armed to the teeth to the mix and you have a deadly combination that even the 3 Little Kittens can't fight their way out of! Plus, an intimate date between Jon and Tarot takes an unexpected turn!
name: Kittens vs. Robots, Part Two of Three: Drone On

Coffin Fly rises again to join The Unforgiving Eye in a race against time as The Red Menace launches an attack on planet Earth. But who is really behind this nefarious plan for world domination? Could it be that we are all no more than playthings in the hands of a 10-year-old sociopath?
name: As Flies to Wanton Boys...

description:
"ORIGIN," Part Two

A second anthology of short stories set in the CARBON GREY universe. A boy becomes a god in 'Gottfaust,' mysterious events are investigated by 'Marshal and Marshall' and a refugee becomes a queen in the tale of 'Raisa.' Legends, secret histories and continuity errors - all will be revealed in CARBON GREY: ORIGINS.
name: Origin, Part Two

description: Shotgun City's real scumbags are finally exposed, and Johnny Jackson is hell-bent on making sure they get what's coming to them. Trouble is, they're not going out without a fight? Is Johnny as doomed as some of his closest allies, or will justice finally prevail? It's a startling conclusion to one of 2010's wildest books!
name: "...I Dreamt I'd Never Sleep Again"

description:
King Conan has built his empire by brawn and by blade, but there are dangers that lurk in the shadows of his throne that cannot be slain by the Cimmerian's steel. Assassins are at his chamber door, and Thoth-Amon-back to the height of his power-is summoning fearsome fiends from the fiery pit! If he is to survive the night, Conan will need to enlist the aid of the gods!

Number 7 in a series.
name: A Servant for My Hate

volume.name: King Conan: The Phoenix on the Sword

description: Super Dinosaur and Derek Dynamo must team up with the dreaded Squidious - one of their most fearsome foes, in order to defeat The EXILE! If his master plan cannot be thwarted, all of humanity is lost!

Extreme's zombie-black op-superheroes return! Cabbot Stone is the last unliving Bloodstrike agent, an unstoppable weapon in America's war on terror! But being dead is a hell of way to make a living, and Cabbot is losing his faith. Will his latest mission be his last? Bloody horror-action with heart by Hack/Slash writer Tim Seeley and Artist Franchesco Gaston!

Brand New Comic Strip: 'Megatron's Law'

Will Starscream survive the Decepticon leader's fiery fighting pit? Read this issue's awesome TRANSFORMERS PRIME comic strip and find out!

Smackdown: Bulkhead Vs Arcee

Arcee loves Bulkhead, even though his clumsiness and general goofiness can annoy the heck into her. What would happen if he pushed her too far? We provide the stats - you decide who wins the smackdown!

Episode Guide: Scrapheap

Check out our guide to the episode where the Autobots find a mysterious pod in the Arctic. Back at base the pod breaks open releasing a horde of scraplets - who wreak havoc on the base!
name: Megatron's Law

description:
Valiant annual outwith the normal annual run, themed around magic, horror and weird suspense style stories. It starred Sylvester Turville, the Spellbinder.

Contents:

  • The Hand of Tuthoon - Spellbinder comic strip in colour
  • This Evil Place
  • The Great movie Monster Quiz - feature
  • The Final Victim - comic strip in vein of EC "twist in the tale" horror stories, by Pat Mills, Derek Cribbling and Joe Colquhoun.
  • The Dracula Dynasty - feature on different depictions of Dracula
  • Creature from Nowhere - Spellbinder comic strip
  • The Red House
  • It's a Weird World
  • The Spellbinder (Part 1) - Spellbinder comic strip reprinted from Lion
  • Screaming Skulls - feature about real world ghostly legends tied to human skulls
  • The Magic Spectacles - Spellbinder text strip
  • The Horrors of Turville Hall - Spellbinder comic strip
  • Stranger than Fiction - feature
  • The Passing of Gallantyne Gox - comic strip in vein of EC "twist in the tale" horror stories
  • The Spellbinder (Part 2) - Spellbinder comic strip reprinted from Lion
  • Nightmare
  • The Fugitive from the Future - Spellbinder text story
  • The Terror in the Fog - comic strip in vein of EC "twist in the tale" horror stories
  • The Laughter from Beyond
  • The Night of the Gargoyle - Spellbinder comic strip in colour
  • They Mystified Millions - feature on famous illusionists, magicians and escapologists such as Harry Houdini, the Great Lafayette and Chung Ling Soo.
  • The Man on the Road - comic strip in vein of EC "twist in the tale" horror stories
  • The Spellbinder (Part 3) - Spellbinder comic strip reprinted from Lion
  • "Of Thee She'll Sing..." - text story by J.R. Montague, illustrated by Geoff Campion
  • The Strange Old House by the Churchyard - comic strip in vein of EC "twist in the tale" horror stories
